cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper uses computer vision techniques to classify force exertion levels based on face videos and photoplethysmography signals. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with human-computer interaction and ergonomics, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the use of PPG signals could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with health and well-being. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for classification, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
